commitResults.messageTitle: Jaanu.java: Rename from Duke and revise greeting message
Jaanu.java: Personalize chatbot and add input functionality

Jaanu.java: Add manageTasks functionality and refactor code - Chatbot can now store tasks when inputted by user. - Chatbot responds to 'list' command by listing all tasks inputted by   user. - Refactor code to use OOP by adding printGreeting, printBye, printList   to ensure readibility and better debugging.
Jaanu.java: Add mark and unmark functionality so users can track progress
Refactor code to use Task class to represent task list
Refactor code to comply with A-CodingStandard
commitResults.messageBody:
- Reformatted code to follow the coding standard guidelines
- Updated variable naming conventions for consistency
- Adjusted indentation and spacing throughout codebase
- Ensured method and class structures align with standard requirements

commitResults.messageTitle: Add support for ToDo, Event, and Deadline tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
- Implemented three task classes: ToDo, Event, and Deadline
- ToDo: tasks without date/time attachment
- Event: tasks with start and end date/time
- Deadline: tasks with a due date/time
- Updated task creation and storage to handle different task types

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor the code to follow object-oriented design principles by improving modularity and encapsulation
Add print error message capabilities in JaanuException class
Add comprehensive error handling for user input validation
commitResults.messageBody:
Implement JaanuException custom exception class to handle all possible
error cases with specific, user-friendly error messages. Enhanced input
validation across all commands with detailed feedback and usage examples.

Changes:
- Validate empty descriptions for todo/deadline/event commands
- Validate mark/unmark commands (missing index, invalid number, out of range)
- Check for already marked/unmarked tasks to prevent redundant operations
- Validate deadline must include date with "/" separator
- Validate event must include both start and end times
- Handle empty input and unknown commands with helpful messages
- Add error check for empty list display
- Add error check for full task list (MAX_TASKS limit)
- Provide usage examples in error messages for better UX
